The Henry Tax Review described the asymmetry between gains and losses as ``among the greatest tax-induced biases to the savings choices of households.''\footcite[p.~69]{Treasury2010} This runs counter to the rationale for allowing the deductibility of losses -- to maintain tax neutrality of debt and equity financing.

